  <title>Triples and Solutions</title>

  <p> Consider an ordered triple of integers <m> (e_1, e_2, e_3) </m>. To this triple, we associate the differencess
  <m> A = e_2 - e_1 </m>,
  <m> B = e_3 - e_2 </m>, and 
  <m> C = e_1 - e_3 </m>.
  </p>

